# demos/doom/doom.sources: maize-145 DOOM Phase A source listfile
#
# The platform-agnostic doomgeneric + DOOM translation units for a headless
# Maize build, consumed by scripts/cc-maize.sh via --sources. One repo-relative
# path per line; blank lines and lines beginning with # are skipped.
#
# Vendored submodule: demos/doom/doomgeneric (github.com/ozkl/doomgeneric),
# pinned commit dcb7a8dbc7a16ce3dda29382ac9aae9d77d21284 ("boolean fix").
#
# Derivation: this set is the SDL Makefile's SRC_DOOM list (the canonical DOOM +
# doomgeneric object set) MINUS the three SDL-specific TUs:
#   doomgeneric_sdl.c  (the SDL platform backend; replaced by demos/doom/doomgeneric_maize.c)
#   i_sdlsound.c       (reaches for host SDL audio; residual DG_sound_module stubbed in doomgeneric_maize.c)
#   i_sdlmusic.c       (reaches for host SDL_mixer; residual DG_music_module stubbed in doomgeneric_maize.c)
# All other per-platform backends (doomgeneric_{allegro,emscripten,linuxvt,soso,
# sosox,win,xlib}.c) and alternate sound backends are simply not in SRC_DOOM and
# so are not listed here.
#
# This file names NO entry `main` TU, so Phase C can reuse it verbatim for the
# headless self-check; the Phase A entry (demos/doom/doom_main.c) and the stub
# platform (demos/doom/doomgeneric_maize.c) are passed alongside it on the
# command line, not listed here.
#
